00:39:03,960 --> 00:39:06,600
"When will I get more?
When will I get more?"

00:39:06,600 --> 00:39:08,760
so the $75,000 today,
I'm assuming,

00:39:08,760 --> 00:39:10,130
is all going to buy inventory?

00:39:10,130 --> 00:39:11,960
Yes.
Okay.

00:39:11,960 --> 00:39:13,130
You're successful.

00:39:13,130 --> 00:39:16,260
You're giving up 10% today
for $75,000.

00:39:16,260 --> 00:39:17,800
What happens tomorrow?

00:39:17,800 --> 00:39:21,460
It sounds like the business
isn't generating enough cash

00:39:21,460 --> 00:39:22,860
for you to buy inventory.

00:39:22,860 --> 00:39:27,230
What if you need another $75,000
or $200,000 or $500,000?

00:39:27,230 --> 00:39:29,530
There's gotta be a different way
to build this business

00:39:29,530 --> 00:39:31,760
than every time you grow,

00:39:31,760 --> 00:39:34,600
having to sell equity
