husband who went to annapolis,

00:40:12,700 --> 00:40:15,300
and I think I'm gonna trade
him in and marry you instead.

00:40:15,300 --> 00:40:17,360
(mark and Robert laugh)
But I am troubled

00:40:17,360 --> 00:40:20,360
by the, uh, $240,000 invested.

00:40:20,360 --> 00:40:23,730
It seems like a lot of money
for where you stand right now.

00:40:23,730 --> 00:40:25,560
I'm also troubled by the fact
that you have...

00:40:25,560 --> 00:40:27,830
43% interest?
Yes.

00:40:27,830 --> 00:40:29,760
And you're willing to give away
another 10%, which puts you--

00:40:29,760 --> 00:40:31,860
I just feel like you're
eating away at the company

00:40:31,860 --> 00:40:33,330
and don't have enough
to show for it.

00:40:33,330 --> 00:40:35,330
But everybody gets diluted,
not him.
(Robert) Yeah.

00:40:35,330 --> 00:40:36,760
Yeah, okay, but I'm out.

00:40:40,630 --> 00:40:42,400
The story's very powerful.

00:40:42,400 --> 00:40:46,530
It's good enough for a sniper
on the battlefield,

00:40:46,530 --> 00:40:48,430
and I want the same product
for me.

00:40:48,430 --> 00:40:51,630
This whole jittery finger thing,
caffeine--I buy into 100%.

00:40:51,630 --> 00:40:53,900
I get it. Everybody'll get that
right away.

00:40:53,900 --> 00:40:58,760
Normally, I would want more,

00:40:58,760 --> 00:41:00,100
but I like it a lot.

00:41:00,100 --> 00:41:01,960
This is very uncharacteristic
of me.

00:41:01,960 --> 00:41:03,730
I'll give you what you want.

00:41:03,730 --> 00:41:05,560
What?!

00:41:05,560 --> 00:41:06,730
I'll give you 75k for 10%.

00:41:08,730 --> 00:41:11,730
I'll simplify things.
I love the idea.

00:41:11,730 --> 00:41:14,130
I-I'd love the opportunity
to invest in you.

00:41:14,130 --> 00:41:16,460
The problem is,
I only get half of you.

00:41:18,200 --> 00:41:20,800
Business doesn't work
after 4:00 p.m. Time,

00:41:20,800 --> 00:41:22,700
and it doesn't work
on a schedule.

00:41:22,700 --> 00:41:25,800
And when things have to happen,
they have to happen.

00:41:25,800 --> 00:41:28,830
You've gotta be there
when the business needs you,

00:41:28,830 --> 00:41:30,330
and I don't see that
as being possible right now,

00:41:30,330 --> 00:41:32,830
so for that reason, I'm out.

00:41:32,830 --> 00:41:34,560
Okay. Understood.

00:41:34,560 --> 00:41:36,460
Well, rob, here's what I know.

00:41:36,460 --> 00:41:38,000
Marines always find a way.

00:41:38,000 --> 00:41:39,500
They do.

00:41:39,500 --> 00:41:42,160
So I'm not bothered by the fact
you--You have a full-Time job

00:41:42,160 --> 00:41:44,300
serving the country until 4:00.

00:41:44,300 --> 00:41:46,660
But I think you're gonna need
more cash

00:41:46,660 --> 00:41:48,600
than the $75,000.

00:41:48,600 --> 00:41:50,960
So... Here's what I'm thinking.

00:41:50,960 --> 00:41:52,860
If Kevin will have me--

00:41:52,860 --> 00:41:56,230
$150,000 from the two of us

00:41:56,230 --> 00:41:58,360
for 20%.

00:41:58,360 --> 00:42:01,600
You know what? Robert's right.
You need more cash.

00:42:01,600 --> 00:42:03,100
I'll do that deal with him.

00:42:03,100 --> 00:42:06,500
Now you've just doubled
what you came in here for.

00:42:12,160 --> 00:42:14,700
I appreciate it.
I'll take $150,000 for 20%

00:42:14,700 --> 00:42:17,230
from Mr. O'Leary
and Mr. Herjavec.
(Robert and Kevin) All right!

00:42:17,230 --> 00:42:19,060
(mark) Congratulations, guys.
First thing we do is
we Mount operations,

00:42:19,060 --> 00:42:21,760
take out both of his drinks.
(Barbara laughs)

00:42:21,760 --> 00:42:22,930
Thanks, guys.
Really appreciate it.
Yeah, thank you.

00:42:22,930 --> 00:42:24,600
Thank you very much.
Congrats, rob.

00:42:24,600 --> 00:42:26,000
Thanks, guys.
(Robert) Yeah, thanks.

00:42:28,700 --> 00:42:31,030
Team ruckpack is hugely excited
about this deal.

00:42:31,030 --> 00:42:34,330
With twice as much money,
we can kick twice as much ass.

